commitResults.messageBody:
Added exceptions.
Added error handling.
Added input validation (not very extensive).
Added support for deleting tasks from the list.
Added support for deleting tasks from the list.

Added input/output redirection bash script to semi-automate testing of Duke
Modified bash script for use with different input/output pairs
deleted redundant test input file

Added support for saving the task list between sessions
Added a sample list (src/main/java/DukeSaveFile.txt)
Added support for parsing time in "dd/MM/yyyy HHmm" pattern (strictly in this pattern without deviation).

Added functionality to TaskList for loading and saving to/from different files (actual path still hard coded into Duke.java)
Added basic exceptions for Loading Saving from file path/file errors
changes made to Duke.java and TaskList.java were not properly staged in previous commit
Fixed incorrect integer ordinal postfix when parsing day of month

extracted closely related code into same classes

	new file:   UserInterface.java
	- deals with iteraction between user and duke

 	modified:   Parser.java
	- deals with interpreting/filtering user input into information useable by duke

 	modified:   Output.java
	- deals with printing output

	new file:   Storage.java
	- extracted loading saving functionality to upper level class
	- handles file reading and writing

	modified:   Command.java
	- changed Command from enum to class
	- changed to containers for commands and parameters

	new file:   AddTaskCommand.java
	- extracted commands for making different task to an upper level class

	new file:   CompleteTaskCommand.java
	- extracted done command to an upper level class

	new file:   DeleteTaskCommand.java
	- extracted delete command to an upper level class

	new file:   ShowListCommand.java
	- extracted list command to an upper level class

	new file:   ExitCommand.java
	- extracated bye command to an upper level class

 	new file:   SaveFiles/DukeSave01.txt
	- save file for content of list between sessions

grouped related classes together:
-classes meant for I/O
-classes related to Command
-classes related to Tasks

Added ShadowJar plugin to project to help create .jar executable
'com.github.johnrengelman.shadow' version '5.1.0'
Added support for searching for a keyword  in tasklist
cleaned up code to match coding standard (less comments)

Added JavaDoc comments to the source files
Deleted some unused classes

Merged modification to code to conform to coding standards into master branch
Fixed some parts where it did not conform to coding standards in the master branch

Use .fxml files for the basic design of the GUI (from the provided tutorial)

Repackage classes to be more logical
- e.g. Parser in duke.command instead of duke.io

Remove redundant classes
- Input, Output: no longer using command line for input and output

Add JUnit tests for new methods for Duke.
Use the provided checkstyle.xml file from gradle branch to check for coding style violations using checkstyle plugin.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix GUI to properly display file missing error
commitResults.messageBody:
GUI now displays whether the TaskList can be loaded from the specified file path.
If the file path is invalid, and cannot be made, Duke now deactivates.

Add assertions to check that arguments that should not be null should be non-null.
Add assertions that delete, complete commands should have int argument > 0.

commitResults.messageBody:
Fix JUnit tests methods which were broken by introducing Java assertions.

Remove some redundant assertions

commitResults.messageBody:
Previously task list save file would be read from and written to resource directory,
this causes Duke to be unable to save task list when run from jar as the jar is locked.

Change so that a new directory in the directory the jar is contained in to be created,
and save files read to and written from there.
